@L'osservatore--the 2nd amendment says nothing about resisting the U.S. government, as you can read above.  It does say a militia was authorized only to ensure the security of a free State.  That we now live in a free state is open to debate, and the idea of anarchy has doubtless crossed people's minds over the decades.   

The 2nd amendment authorizes only "A well regulated militia, being necessary to the security of a free State,..."  It does not even authorize personal ownership of weapons.  It authorizes a well-regulated militia.  The issue of gun ownership is not discussed.  A well regulated militia could have its arms stored under lock and key unless our "free State" was attacked.  

And yes, voters decide the future of the U.S., provided those elected actually listen to them.
